The paper proposes a deep neural network framework for large-scale spatial time series forecasting problems. The paper focuses on designing a neural network architecture for capturing various types of patterns, such as short-term, long-term, and spatial patterns. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which is the primary focus of the paper. Additionally, the paper uses fuzzy clustering, which is a common technique in unsupervised learning, and denoising autoencoder, which is a common technique in deep learning. Therefore, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also deals with spatial data, which can be analyzed using computer vision techniques such as convolutional neural networks. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with time series forecasting, which can be considered a sub-field of statistical inference. Therefore, cs.SI (Statistics and Machine Learning) is also a possible sub-category.
